%% Data Flow Diagram for odh-model-controller
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as odh-model-controller<br/>Controller Manager
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant GWServer as Gateway Discovery Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Dashboard as RHOAI Dashboard
    participant Router as OpenShift Router
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant Kuadrant as Kuadrant / Authorino
    participant Istio as Istio
    participant NIMAPI as NVIDIA NIM API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry

    Note over User, K8sAPI: Flow 1: InferenceService Deployment (RawDeployment)
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply InferenceService<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-...-inferenceservice<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated (name length, namespace check)
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: ISVC created<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create OpenShift Route<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create metrics Service + ServiceMonitor<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterRoleBinding<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Note right of Controller: Route: Edge or Reencrypt TLS

    Note over User, Kuadrant: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Auth Policy Setup
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: LLMInferenceService created<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create AuthPolicy (Gateway-level)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create AuthPolicy (HTTPRoute-level)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create EnvoyFilter (Authorino TLS)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Note right of Controller: Auth enforced by Kuadrant/Authorino

    Note over Dashboard, GWServer: Flow 3: Gateway Discovery
    Dashboard->>GWServer: GET /api/v1/gateways?namespace=X<br/>HTTPS/8443, Bearer Token
    GWServer->>K8sAPI: SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443, User's Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>GWServer: Allowed/Denied
    GWServer->>K8sAPI: List Gateways<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>GWServer: Gateway list
    GWServer-->>Dashboard: Filtered Gateways (JSON)<br/>HTTPS/8443

    Note over User, NIMAPI: Flow 4: NIM Account Integration
    User->>K8sAPI: Create NIM Account CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-nim-...-account<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: Account created
    Controller->>NIMAPI: Validate API Key + Fetch catalog<br/>HTTPS/443, NGC API Key
    NIMAPI-->>Controller: Model catalog data
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (NIM config)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret (pull secret)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Template (runtime)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token

    Note over User, Controller: Flow 5: Ray TLS Certificate Management
    User->>K8sAPI: Create multi-node ServingRuntime<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: ServingRuntime created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ray-ca-tls Secret (self-signed CA)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ray-tls Secret (CA cert)<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    Note over K8sAPI, Webhook: Pod creation triggers webhook
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate--v1-pod<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated (inject Ray TLS init-container)
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event: Pod created (RAY_USE_TLS)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update ray-tls with per-pod cert<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
